      <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
         <head altrender="organization" id="a2">ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY </head>
         <p>Since its founding in 1913, the Young Women's Hospital Aid was a social organization
            whose prime function was fund raising for the Tompkins County Hospital. Officers and
            members of this group were usually prominent women of the Ithaca, New York area. The Aid
            assisted in the purchase of equipment for the hospital, and helped provide for the
            comfort and well-being of its patients. The organization also funded nursing
            scholarships with money raised through charity balls, fashion shows, and other social
            events. In 1964 the organization was dissolved and absorbed into the hospital's
            Department of Volunteer Services.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Collection includes reports of the Young Women's Hospital Aid Charity Ball, 1913-1963;
            minutes of the General Meeting, 1946-1963; correspondence, 1961-1964; mimeographed
            newsletters to members, 1961-1963; Special Committee minutes and reports, 1962-1963; and
            miscellaneous newspaper clippings, pamphlets, and other records.</p>
      </scopecontent>
